cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper proposes a deep neural network architecture for indoor localization based on Wi-Fi fingerprinting. This involves classification of building/floor/location and estimation of floor-level coordinates. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves image processing techniques for feature extraction, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of the proposed architecture for mobile devices suggests a possible fit with cs.SY (Systems and Control).
